This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with password security and guessing attacks. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it proposes a metric for measuring password strength. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it involves assessing the efficiency of guessing attacks. It may also be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as password security is an important aspect of software development. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Cybersecurity) as it deals with password security and attacks.
